<h1>Smart Board Templates for Teachers</h1>
[/fusion_text][fusion_text]Smartboard technology is a fast growing interactive tool used in schools as a new teaching technique. This state of the art electronic board does not replace chalk boards or white boards but enhances teaching tools. This is a new technology with new software and can be a little daunting for the beginner. Listed below is a resource page to help you get started and templates to download. There is also a blog page with teacher comments, the results of their experience with the smartboard, and even downloadable templates of their favorite lesson.

<strong>K-2</strong>
<ul>
	<li>Smart: Downloadable templates for grades k-3.</li>
	<li>Portaportal: A cool site with smartboard templates in all grades, mostly k-5</li>
	<li>Kidspiration: Great site with nice downloadable templates for k-2.</li>
	<li>Center School District: Templates for downloading.</li>
	<li>Smartboards in the Classroom: Nice templates for k-2 and more.</li>
	<li>Shadow Oaks Elementary: Smartboards templates.</li>
</ul>
<strong>3-5</strong>
<ul>
	<li>Educator's Summer Symposium: A beginner's guide to using Smartboard and templates to help get started.</li>
	<li>Oklahoma lessons: Agricultural templates.</li>
	<li>Smart technology sites: A list of sites featuring templates for downloading by grade.</li>
	<li>Eduscapes: Teaching kids the smartboard way!</li>
	<li>Garnet Valley School District: A listing of smartboard templates.</li>
	<li>Smartboard: Fifth grade language arts templates. Plus templates for all grades and subjects.</li>
	<li>ismartboards:: Listing of visual aids and smartboard templates.</li>
</ul>
<strong>Middle School</strong>
<ul>
	<li>Technology Integrated: A huge listing of smartboard resources.</li>
	<li>Wichita public schools: Smartboard lessons.</li>
	<li>EduTech: tutorials for smartboards.</li>
	<li>Constructive Celebration!: Smartboard information and templates.</li>
	<li>Smartboard Lessons: A list of lessons using Smartboard.</li>
	<li>Curriki: An interactive meeting place where each teachers posts their comments AND the downloadable template! They even give examples of what works best for them!</li>
	<li>Ardsley Middle School: Smartboard game templates.</li>
	<li>Smartboard templates: Savable science smartboard lessons.</li>
</ul>
<strong>High School</strong>
<ul>
	<li>Technology Standards: smartboard templates for 9-12<sup>th</sup> grade.</li>
	<li>National Library of Virtual Ideas: Templates for smartboard and interactive use.</li>
	<li>East Carter School: Resource templates for 9-12<sup>th</sup> grade.</li>
	<li>Jefferson County Schools: Interactive smartboard templates</li>
	<li>Smartboard: An all inclusive page to smartboard tutorials and templates.</li>
	<li>Grosse Point North High School: A video demonstration on the use of the smartboard and templates.</li>
	<li>Wright City School District: a list of downloadable smartboard templates.</li>
</ul>
<strong>Special School</strong>
<ul>
	<li>Kentucky School for the Deaf: smartboard templates for special needs classes.</li>
	<li>SmartEd Services: Special needs templates for the smartboard.</li>
	<li>Teq: A list of downloadable templates.</li>
	<li>Priory Woods School: An expansive list of templates. This is their top twenty list of most popular downloads.</li>
</ul>
